(FILE: docs/data_quality.md) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(```markdown) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(# Basic GTFS data quality) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The silver validator checks whether core tables and columns exist, reports row counts, and) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(detects:) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- missing key values and duplicate stop, route, or trip identifiers;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- invalid stop latitude and longitude;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- uncommon or invalid obvious `route_type` values;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- invalid arrival and departure time syntax, including support for valid hours above 23;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- stop times referencing unknown trips or stops;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- trips referencing unknown routes or service identifiers.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Status meanings) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- **PASS**: the check found no problems.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- **WARN**: the data deserves review, but the condition may be an extension or a usable) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(non-critical value. The route-type range check uses this status.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- **FAIL**: a required structure, value, format, uniqueness rule, or relationship has a) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(detected problem.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The report's overall status is the most severe individual status. Validation reports) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(findings without modifying silver data or stopping merely because a check fails.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Limitations) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(This is educational, basic validation rather than complete GTFS certification. It does not) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(implement the full GTFS Schedule specification, conditional field requirements, geographic) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(plausibility within Toulouse, ordering rules, schedule consistency, shape validation,) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(translated feeds, or every extended route type. It counts problems but does not include) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(potentially sensitive or very large lists of affected rows. A dedicated standards validator) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(would still be appropriate before production publication.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(```) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(docs/data_source.md) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
