0 -11.00 Td
(## Scheduled departures by route and hour) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents one route, service date, and service-day hour. Only the minimum) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(`stop_sequence` for each trip is counted, so the value represents trip starts rather than) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(all station calls. GTFS hours after midnight remain 24, 25, and so on.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Scheduled stop departures by day) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents one stop on one service date. Every stop-time departure with a usable) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(departure time is counted, giving the planned activity at that stop.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Network daily summary) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents a service date and reports active routes, scheduled trips, scheduled stop) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(departures, and active stops. It is a compact overview of the scheduled network supply.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Route period summary) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents one route over the full GTFS service period. It reports active service) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(days, total scheduled trips, average trips per active day, maximum daily trips, and the) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(first and last service dates. Use this table when saying "top routes over the GTFS service) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(period".) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Planned hourly headway) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents one route, service date, and service-day hour. `planned_headway_minutes`) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(is `60 / scheduled_departures_count`. This is an approximate planned headway from the static) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(schedule, not real passenger waiting time.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Route type daily summary) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(One row represents one service date and GTFS route type. It reports active routes, scheduled) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(trips, and scheduled stop departures for labels such as Tram, Subway/Metro, Bus, and other) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(standard GTFS route types. Unknown route types are labelled Unknown.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Busiest route/day) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(This table keeps the top 50 individual route/day combinations by scheduled trips. It is) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(useful for evidence because it avoids mixing a per-day peak with a full-period total.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Busiest stop/day) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(This table keeps the top 50 individual stop/day combinations by scheduled departures. It) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(identifies high-activity planned stop days, not observed passenger demand.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Service calendars) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Regular weekday service is expanded between `start_date` and `end_date`. A `calendar_dates`) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(exception type 1 adds service; type 2 removes it. If only `calendar_dates` exists, additions) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(define the available dates.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why these are not reliability KPIs) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Static GTFS says what should run, not what actually happened. These KPIs measure planned) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(supply and establish a comparison baseline. Future real-time observations could add actual) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(arrivals, delays, cancellations, headway regularity, and planned-versus-observed) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(reliability. Those concerns are intentionally outside the current phase.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
