(# GTFS-Realtime exploration) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## What GTFS-Realtime is) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(GTFS-Realtime is the live companion to static GTFS. Static GTFS describes the planned offer.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(GTFS-Realtime describes operational information observed around fetch time.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Common GTFS-Realtime feed entity types are:) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Trip Updates: changes or predictions for trips and stop times.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Vehicle Positions: vehicle location and status information.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Service Alerts: disruptions, messages, and informed routes, stops, or trips.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Tisseo context) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The official transport.data.gouv.fr dataset page states that Tisseo publishes GTFS-RT data) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(and lists a combined `GtfsRt.pb` resource containing TripUpdate and Alert entities, plus an) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(`Alert.pb` resource containing alerts. Vehicle Positions are not listed as available there,) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(so the project leaves the vehicle positions URL unset unless a reliable official endpoint is) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(provided later.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why snapshots first) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(This phase fetches one protobuf file and saves it unchanged as `feed.pb`. That file is a) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(deterministic local snapshot. It can be reused for:) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- parser tests;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- replay experiments;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- demos without live internet;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- static/live compatibility checks.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(This is intentionally not continuous streaming. There is no Kafka, Spark, Airflow, database,) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(API, dashboard, or cloud service in this phase.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why static/live compatibility matters) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Future real-time reliability indicators need joins between live observations and static) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(schedule data. Before building those indicators, the project must answer whether live) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(`route_id`, `trip_id`, and `stop_id` values can be matched to the silver static GTFS tables.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The compatibility report measures how many identifiers match and how many are unmatched.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Perfect matching is not required during exploration, but the result shows whether the feed) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(is a candidate for later real-time phases.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## What the real-time gold layer adds) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The real-time gold layer combines one parsed Trip Updates snapshot with the static silver) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(GTFS tables. It creates:) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- feed health indicators;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- enriched trip update rows with static route and trip match flags;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- route delay snapshot indicators;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- stop delay snapshot indicators;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- identifier compatibility percentages;) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- static PNG charts and a teacher-facing Markdown report.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(These are snapshot indicators observed at fetch time, not continuous real-time reliability) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(metrics.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why trip ID mismatch can happen) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Trip IDs can fail to match when the selected static GTFS run does not exactly correspond to) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(the real-time publication, when operational trips are represented differently in real-time,) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(or when the real-time feed exposes partial or modified trip descriptors. This is why the) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(project keeps unmatched trip rows instead of dropping them.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why route IDs and stop IDs still matter) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Route and stop identifiers are often more stable than trip identifiers. If `route_id` and) Tj
ET
