(```markdown) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(# Teacher presentation notes) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Simple explanation) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Mobility Control Tower is a local Data Engineering platform for public transport data. It) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(transforms official transport files into validated tables, KPIs, reports, an API, and a) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(dashboard.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Public transport data) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(Public transport data describes stops, routes, trips, schedules, and sometimes live service) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(updates.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## GTFS Schedule) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(GTFS Schedule is the planned offer: where stops are, which routes exist, and what trips are) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(scheduled.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## GTFS-Realtime) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(GTFS-Realtime is operational data observed around fetch time. In this project it is handled) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(as saved snapshots, not streaming.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Pipeline) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(The pipeline preserves raw files, creates bronze copies, cleans silver tables, validates) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(quality, computes gold KPIs, serves data through DuckDB and FastAPI, then displays a local) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(dashboard.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(## Why raw, bronze, silver, gold) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
() Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Raw: immutable source evidence.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Bronze: extracted source files.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Silver: cleaned canonical tables.) Tj
0 -11.00 Td
(- Gold: analytical data products.) Tj
ET
endstream
